 continent but a desire to travel to its wonderful places and spaces and purchase curated items in our Boutique and Gallery.\n\n<b>BRAND</b>\n\n<b>HTWE</b> is the insider\'s safari guide with a global outlook, delivering safari style, travel and online shopping in a beautifully designed digital space. HTWE inspires people to experience an African safari by showcasing quality safari-related content that is both beautiful and creative.\n\n<b>CONTENT</b>\n\nOur website features a diverse range of quality content, that aims to inspire all world travellers who use the internet to research and book travel in Africa.\n\n<u><b>THEMES</b></u>\n\nART | DESIGN AND DECOR | EVENTS | FASHION &amp; ACCESSORIES | FOOD | LITERATURE | LODGES PHOTOGRAPHY | PEOPLE | TRAVEL\n\n| TRENDS | TIPS &amp; ADVICE | WEDDINGS | WILDLIFE\n\n<u><b>COUNTRIES</b></u>\n\nBOTSWANA | BURUNDI | KENYA |NAMIBIA | MALAWI | MOZAMBIQUE | RWANDA\n\nSOUTH AFRICA | SWAZILAND | TANZANIA | UGANDA | ZAMBIA | ZIMBABWE\n\n&nbsp;','Advertise','','inherit','open','open','','8-autosave-v1','','','2015-07-08 07:23:16','2015-07-08 07:23:16','',8,'http://htwe.wpengine.com/8-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(14,2,'2015-07-08 07:32:17','2015-07-08 07:32:17','<strong><a href=\"http://htwe.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/out-of-africa-poster.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-49\" src=\"http://htwe.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/out-of-africa-poster-203x300.jpg\" alt=\"out-of-africa-poster\" width=\"203\" height=\"300\" /></a> <a href=\"http://htwe.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/flamingo-scene.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-47\" src=\"http://htwe.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/flamingo-scene-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"flamingo scene\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Out of Africa’s Gipsy Moth returns to Africa</strong>\r\n\r\nBy: Katheer Ontong<!--more-->\r\n\r\nG-AAMY earned her stripes in 1985 when she starred in <strong>\'Out of Africa\'</strong> (link: http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0089755/), the Oscar-winning film starring Meryl Streep and Robert Redford. Jochen Zeitz, owner of Segera Retreat and founder of the <strong>Zeitz Foundation</strong> (ink: http://www.zeitzfoundation.org/) bought the majestic biplane in an auction that was held in Paris in 2013.\r\n\r\nThis beauty is more than just an aviator’s dream; it’s the Gypsy Moth that stole the hearts of many in its hours of soaring over the vast landscapes in Kenya. It is a collector’s piece from 1929, reminiscent of a bygone era of Kenya’s first pioneer explorers. It is also a collector’s piece for Jochen Zeitz who now cherishes the sentimental value it carries for Kenya and Segera guests are able to view and appreciate it when visiting his safari lodge.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo many memories are stapled to the few minutes when it soared across a Rift Valley lake over a profusion of pink flamingos and became the most recognized feature of pioneer Denys Finch Hatton and Karen Blixen passionate romance.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>5 things you didn’t know about the Gypsy Moth:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The biplane was flown for approximately 50 hours of filming.</li>\r\n	<li>The pilot in the scene where the flamingos take flight was Sir Henry Dalrymple-White, a British Baronet and former WW2 pilot who moved to Kenya in the 1940s. He flew until he was 80.</li>\r\n	<li>It is claimed that the yellow Gypsy Moth was sold at an auction for $302,000.</li>\r\n	<li>It has the registration letters, G-AAMY but in the film, the letters are altered slightly to G-AAMT.</li>\r\n	<li>The plane was constructed with a plywood frame, covered with little more than cloth fabric.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n(Source: www.jerrygarrett.wordpress.com)\r\n\r\nIf viewing the Out of Africa memorabilia tickles your fancy or if you\'re a history fanatic, make your way to <strong>Segera Retreat </strong>(link: http://www.segera.com/) and experience the best of both worlds.\r\n\r\nLocation: Laikipia Plateau, Kenya | East Africa\r\n\r\n<u>Videos:</u>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong> Re-assembling the G-AAMY plane at Segera</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n(link: https://vimeo.com/98004861)\r\n\r\n<strong>EMBED CODE </strong>\r\n<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/98004861?color=ffffff\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/98004861\">Out of Africa’s G-AAMY Biplane</a> from <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/user28987494\">Segera Retreat</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li><strong> Out of Africa &amp; Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n(Link: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rjzf_cWzlp8\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rjzf_cWzlp8</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>EMBED CODE</strong>\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Rjzf_cWzlp8\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>','Out of Africa’s Gipsy Moth returns to Africa','','publish','open','open','','out-of-africas-gipsy-moth-returns-to-africa','','','2015-07-08 08:42:30','2015-07-08 08:42:30','',0,'http://htwe.wpengine.com/?p=14',0,'post','',0),(16,2,'2015-07-08 07:38:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2015-07-08 07:38:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://htwe.wpengine.com/?p=16',0,'post','',0),(17,2,'2015-07-08 07:39:27','2015-07-08 07:39:27','','Safari Travel and Lifestyle','','trash','open','open','','safari-travel-and-lifestyle','','','2015-07-08 07:47:30','2015-07-08 07:47:30','',0,'http://htwe.wpengine.com/?page_id=17',0,'page','',0),(19,2,'2015-07-08 07:43:30','2015-07-08 07:43:30','','Travel & Lifestyle','Safari','publish','open','open','','19','','','2015-07-08 08:03:53','2015-07-08 08:03:53','',0,'http://htwe.wpengine.com/?p=19',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(20,2,'2015-07-08 07:44:36','2015-07-08 07:44:36',' ','','Home','publish','open','o